main event: A sighting of an object in the Atlantic Ocean on February 1, 1960, which was concluded to be a meteor.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 12 seconds,The object was observed to be moving generally southwest,The observer described the object as conforming to the pattern of a missile observation,The sighting involved one object, and it was recorded as a ground-visual observation although it was actually air-visual,There were no photographs included with the report.
location: Atlantic Ocean, North Atlantic Ocean, International Waters
